Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
all_instances(25.10)                                      all_instances(25.10)

Name
       all_instances  -  Returns  a collection of all instances available in a
       design, or all instances of a specified library cell  existing  in  the
       current design

Syntax
       all_instances

       [-help]

       <object>

       [-hierarchical]

       Returns a collection of all instances available in a design, or all in-
       stances of a specified library cell existing in the current design.

       Note:  You cannot use the all_instances command on the top level of the
       design (all_instances [get_design top]).

       However, you can use the command for hierarchical  modules  inside  the
       top  level.  For  example,  if  SUB is a hierarchical module in the top
       level of the design, you can specify the following  command  to  return
       all instances of that module:

       all_instances [get_design SUB].

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -hierarchical
              Specifies that the patterns should be matched hierarchically. If
              the  hierarchical name of an instance at a particular hierarchi-
              cal level matches the patterns, it is included in the result.

       <object>
              Specifies the name of a design or a library cell in the  current
              design. You can specify a pattern for the design or library cell
              name, or a single collection of a design or library cell.

Examples
              * The  following  command  returns  a  collection of all the in-
                stances of the library cell BUF:

                all_instances BUF

              * The following returns a collection of  all  instances  of  the
                sub-module subblock:

                all_instances [get_design subblock]

                subblock_inst1 subblock_inst2

